# Engineering Rules

- On startup, verify that `lua` and `busted` are available. Quality tools are pre-installed under `vendor/` (mutate4lua, crap4lua, dry4lua, arch_view, scrap4lua).
- Work in small, reviewable increments.
- Prefer the simplest design that supports the current behavior and leaves clear options for the next step.
- Keep tests close to the behavior being changed.
- The Gherkin acceptance pipeline is in place under `tools/acceptance/`. Run it with `lua tools/acceptance/run_acceptance.lua`.
- Run the relevant local verification command before handoff whenever the project has one. Use `lua tools/quality/verify_full.lua` for comprehensive quality checks.
- Do not commit unrelated local changes or generated artifacts unless required for the task.
- Before relying on an unfamiliar command, inspect local help or project documentation.
